==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*kunnan-'', from Indo-European ''*gnō-'' ‘to know’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[kunna]], Old Saxon ''cunnan'' (Dutch [[kunnen]]), Old High German [[kunnan]] (German [[können]]), Old Norse [[kunna]] (Swedish [[kunna]]), Gothic [[𐌺𐌿𐌽𐌽𐌰𐌽]].  The IE root is also the source of Greek [[γιγνωσκειν]], Latin [[gnoscere]], Welsh [[gnawd]], Russian [[знать]], Lithuanian [[žinoti]].

